archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: 1 - Set Up Internal Applicant List
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation:
Ability to determine the columns on the list Ability to define the rules to be applied to ranking applicants Ability to create groups into which applicants will fall, and to determine the criteria/threshold for adding applicants to specific groups
* Language outlined below is not finalized and is subject to change.
Facilities Collective Agreement:
FBA Employees within 75 seniority hours of each other: • System flags FBA employees who are listed within 75 seniority hours of each other on the internal Applicant List. • Auto-populates language in the comments field for each employee: *If you are considering this employee or any one below this applicant for this position, please contact Internal Talent Acquisition (link) prior to contacting this applicant. You will be provided with updated seniority hours. • Ability for Hiring Leader to submit automated request for updated seniority hours to internal Talent Acquisition for multiple employees. • Upon receiving the Hiring Leader’s request via workflow, Talent Acquisition triggers a request to Workforce Central : *Please provide the number of seniority hours worked between date after cut-off and the posting closing date (not including overtime hours) for each employee. • Workforce Central provides seniority hours to Talent Acquisition. Talent Acquisition provides Hiring Leader with employee’s updated seniority hours and applicable changes to the internal Applicant List. Qualifying FBA employees for clerical positions: • System to identify if the employee is currently in the same job code as the position they are applying for. • If yes, auto-populates language in the comments field: *Meets requirements of the position. • If employee is not in the same job code, system to display the testing results that the applicant has completed within the last 24 months.
Nurses Collective Agreement:
Employees with the same seniority date: • System flags NBA employees who have the same seniority date on the internal Applicant List. • Auto-populates language in the comments field: *Selection Plan Spreadsheet Required Employed Student Nurses: • System flags Employed Student Nurses and auto-populates their ‘graduation date’ in comments field. (Graduation date inputted on hire requisition). Article 17.02 Temporary Appointments (C): • System identifies employees who are currently working in a temporary assignment and displays the start and end date of the assignment on the internal Applicant List.
• Additional fields required on the internal Applicant List for all CA’s : o Employment Status o Temporary Assignment: Y or N o Temporary Assignment: Start/End Date o Comments Article 18.01 First Consideration: Grades L1, L3, (LOA, LOB Forensics Only) • System automatically flags NBA positions with grades L1, L3, LOA, LOB • Requirement: If the most senior applicant has the same job code and department (current or previous) as the position they are applying to, 17.02 applies and an interview is not required. • Auto-populates language in the comments field: *Based on the revised language in the collective agreement, Talent Acquisition has made a recommendation to support your selection decision: Offer the position to ‘employee’s name’ based on her/his seniority; a formal interview is not required. Please verify that ‘employee’s name’, meets the qualifications. If you have any questions, please follow up with your HR Consultant. (Links to HRC email) Health Science Professionals Collective Agreement
Employees with the same seniority date: • System flags employees who have the same seniority date on the internal Applicant List. • Auto-populates language in the comments field: *Selection Plan Spreadsheet Required Communities Collective Agreement
Employees with the same seniority hours: • System flags employees who have the same seniority hours on the internal Applicant List. • Auto-populates language in the comments field: *Selection Plan Spreadsheet Required Qualifying CBA Employees for Clerical Positions: • System to identify if the employee is currently in the same job code as the position they are applying for. • If yes, auto-populates language in the comments field: *Meets requirements of the position. • If employee is not in the same job code, system to display the testing results that the applicant has completed within the last 24 months.
